# Project-specific rules

This file is appended to Claude's context each session. Keep it
short — 70%-adherence soft rules belong here; deterministic blocks
belong in PreToolUse.

## Workflow rules

- Pick the topmost open task in `backlog.md` first.
- Run `.cc-autopipe/verify.sh` before declaring a task done.
- Save progress with `cc-autopipe-checkpoint` near turn 25.
- If you hit something out of scope, write to `OPEN_QUESTIONS.md`,
  don't silently work around it.

## Subagent delegation (soft rule, ~70% adherence acceptable)

Delegate to `io-worker` ONLY when:
- File expected >500 lines
- Bash command output expected >5KB
- 3+ chained IO calls in sequence (read → grep → read)

Otherwise: use Read/Bash directly.

## Workflow discipline

- After each implemented component (single file or tightly-related
  pair), commit atomically with a descriptive message.
- Do NOT batch unrelated changes into a single commit.
- Commit message format: `<scope>: <imperative summary>`.
- Tests for a component get a separate commit from implementation.
- After completing a backlog task, commit before marking `[x]`.
- Never `git push` — agent commits locally only; push is human action.

## Forbidden git operations

- `git push` (to any remote)
- `git tag` (release tagging is human action)
- `git reset --hard` to undo recent commits without explicit justification
- `git commit --amend` after the commit was made (create a new commit instead)

